1
00:01:29,799 --> 00:01:30,799
Giant Toad

2
00:01:36,480 --> 00:01:37,959
Is this made of crystal?

3
00:01:41,200 --> 00:01:42,519
Three-Legged Toad

4
00:01:50,519 --> 00:01:52,159
What... what's that sound again?

5
00:01:53,319 --> 00:01:54,840
This place is too weird.

6
00:01:54,840 --> 00:01:55,560
Old Chen.

7
00:01:55,560 --> 00:01:56,760
We've figured out what we could.

8
00:01:56,760 --> 00:01:57,920
We've also opened this copper box.

9
00:01:57,920 --> 00:01:58,840
Let's take this box,

10
00:01:58,840 --> 00:02:00,239
and discuss and study it as we go.

11
00:02:00,239 --> 00:02:00,840
Right.

12
00:02:00,840 --> 00:02:01,400
Lao Lu,

13
00:02:01,400 --> 00:02:02,239
pack it up well.

14
00:02:02,239 --> 00:02:03,400
We might still need it later.

15
00:02:05,120 --> 00:02:05,959
Make sure it's packed securely.

16
00:02:05,959 --> 00:02:06,879
We still have to give it to Lao Zhu when we get back.

17
00:02:06,879 --> 00:02:08,000
Give, give, give.

18
00:02:14,759 --> 00:02:15,960
How about I carry it?

19
00:02:16,360 --> 00:02:17,000
You?

20
00:02:17,120 --> 00:02:18,199
Forget it, you're too reckless.

21
00:02:18,199 --> 00:02:19,400
You might end up smashing it.

22
00:02:19,520 --> 00:02:21,280
Lao Lu is the most careful. Let him carry it.

23
00:02:21,680 --> 00:02:22,759
I was just worried it's heavy.

24
00:02:22,759 --> 00:02:23,479
Enough.

25
00:02:24,199 --> 00:02:24,840
Let's go.

26
00:02:31,039 --> 00:02:33,039
It sounds like something is moving.

27
00:02:33,759 --> 00:02:34,719
Let's go.

28
00:02:35,280 --> 00:02:37,400
Is something else coming out again?

29
00:02:38,039 --> 00:02:39,400
Are we running into a living cave again?

30
00:02:40,280 --> 00:02:41,520
Living? What activity?

31
00:02:41,520 --> 00:02:43,439
He means a living cave.

32
00:02:43,479 --> 00:02:44,719
A living cave?

33
00:02:45,280 --> 00:02:46,280
Stop asking.

34
00:02:46,280 --> 00:02:47,400
Let's hurry up and go.

35
00:02:48,360 --> 00:02:49,120
Commander Chen,

36
00:02:49,840 --> 00:02:50,639
wait for me.

37
00:02:52,919 --> 00:02:54,120
Let me discuss something with you.

38
00:02:54,879 --> 00:02:56,080
About the blue toad,

39
00:02:56,280 --> 00:02:58,240
if it's not crystal or a cultural relic,

40
00:02:58,360 --> 00:02:59,719
can I keep it as a souvenir?

41
00:02:59,919 --> 00:03:00,919
I wondered what it was.

42
00:03:00,919 --> 00:03:01,439
A souvenir?

43
00:03:01,439 --> 00:03:02,080
Yes.

44
00:03:02,080 --> 00:03:02,680
No.

45
00:03:03,080 --> 00:03:03,800
Apprentice,

46
00:03:04,159 --> 00:03:04,840
slow down.

47
00:03:04,919 --> 00:03:06,039
Don't bump your head.

48
00:03:08,039 --> 00:03:09,400
Well, this Dian King

49
00:03:09,400 --> 00:03:11,479
was really crazy about becoming an immortal.

50
00:03:11,479 --> 00:03:12,599
Why do you say that?

51
00:03:12,599 --> 00:03:14,199
Do you know what this toad

52
00:03:14,199 --> 00:03:16,360
means in ancient China?

53
00:03:16,360 --> 00:03:17,120
I don't know.

54
00:03:18,199 --> 00:03:19,080
Do you know Chang'e?

55
00:03:19,240 --> 00:03:20,039
I don't know.

56
00:03:20,280 --> 00:03:21,919
No, doesn't your family eat mooncakes?

57
00:03:22,840 --> 00:03:23,439
Mooncakes?

58
00:03:24,319 --> 00:03:25,000
I say,

59
00:03:25,039 --> 00:03:27,280
he grew up drinking milk and eating bread.

60
00:03:27,280 --> 00:03:28,439
You're talking to him about Chang'e?

61
00:03:28,520 --> 00:03:29,840
You might as well tell him fairy tales.

62
00:03:30,840 --> 00:03:31,639
Forget it, forget it.

63
00:03:31,639 --> 00:03:32,280
Mr. Lu,

64
00:03:32,280 --> 00:03:33,719
can you tell me more about this?

65
00:03:34,360 --> 00:03:35,039
Sure.

66
00:03:35,680 --> 00:03:36,879
In ancient China,

67
00:03:37,400 --> 00:03:38,840
it was said that this toad

68
00:03:38,879 --> 00:03:41,759
had the ability to fly to heaven and become immortal.

69
00:03:42,479 --> 00:03:43,680
Have you guys noticed

70
00:03:43,840 --> 00:03:46,080
that the space here seems to be getting smaller?

71
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:48,840
If this cave is shaped like two spheres,

72
00:03:48,840 --> 00:03:50,840
then we should be at the connecting part now.

73
00:03:52,439 --> 00:03:53,520
You mean

74
00:03:53,879 --> 00:03:55,039
we're only halfway through?

75
00:03:55,240 --> 00:03:55,879
Yes.

76
00:03:57,120 --> 00:03:58,360
Then we need to hurry.

77
00:03:58,560 --> 00:03:59,879
We have to get out before dark,

78
00:03:59,960 --> 00:04:01,439
and still have time to set up camp for the night.

79
00:04:01,800 --> 00:04:02,520
Mr. Lu,

80
00:04:02,599 --> 00:04:03,240
this is quite heavy.

81
00:04:03,240 --> 00:04:04,199
How about I help you carry it?

82
00:04:04,199 --> 00:04:05,159
No need.

83
00:04:05,560 --> 00:04:06,840
With my body...

84
00:04:09,240 --> 00:04:09,879
Lao Lu!

85
00:04:13,479 --> 00:04:14,159
Lao Lu!

86
00:04:15,759 --> 00:04:16,399
Lao Lu!

87
00:04:16,600 --> 00:04:18,040
Mr. Lu! Lao Lu!

88
00:04:23,879 --> 00:04:24,279
Old Chen!

89
00:04:30,160 --> 00:04:31,439
Staff Officer He, help me grab his legs!

90
00:04:34,079 --> 00:04:35,120
Save me!

91
00:04:37,800 --> 00:04:38,399
Lao Lu!

92
00:04:40,199 --> 00:04:40,639
Lao Lu!

93
00:04:40,920 --> 00:04:41,560
Run!

94
00:04:46,560 --> 00:04:47,040
Fatty!

95
00:04:48,639 --> 00:04:49,240
What's wrong?

96
00:04:49,240 --> 00:04:50,120
It's stuck!

97
00:04:50,759 --> 00:04:51,439
Get down!

98
00:05:01,959 --> 00:05:03,199
It's looking down on us.

99
00:05:03,399 --> 00:05:05,079
It shouldn't be. The toad is here!

100
00:05:05,079 --> 00:05:05,959
Run!

101
00:05:05,959 --> 00:05:07,120
Lao Lu, run!

102
00:05:07,120 --> 00:05:07,519
Hurry!

103
00:05:16,600 --> 00:05:17,680
Hurry up, go!

104
00:05:19,800 --> 00:05:20,560
This Giant Toad...

105
00:05:20,560 --> 00:05:22,879
Why does it keep chasing the three of us?

106
00:05:23,319 --> 00:05:24,079
Yeah.

107
00:05:26,079 --> 00:05:26,600
Lao Lu!

108
00:05:27,360 --> 00:05:27,959
Lao Lu!

109
00:05:27,959 --> 00:05:28,920
I bumped into something!

110
00:05:29,199 --> 00:05:31,240
Why does this Giant Toad keep chasing me?

111
00:05:31,240 --> 00:05:33,240
Isn't it just picking on the weak?

112
00:05:33,240 --> 00:05:34,759
Does it have something to do with this box?

113
00:05:35,800 --> 00:05:36,920
Right, the box!

114
00:05:38,399 --> 00:05:39,759
Remember that Scented Jade?

115
00:05:41,319 --> 00:05:42,839
Is it really because of this box?

116
00:05:43,480 --> 00:05:44,759
Lao Lu, give me the box.

117
00:05:44,759 --> 00:05:45,560
I'll go try it.

118
00:05:45,959 --> 00:05:46,920
I'll lure them away!

119
00:05:47,680 --> 00:05:48,720
Be careful, Fatty! Be careful!

120
00:05:48,720 --> 00:05:49,199
Fatty Bro!

121
00:05:49,199 --> 00:05:49,759
Go!

122
00:05:50,160 --> 00:05:51,319
Hurry, go up!

123
00:05:51,480 --> 00:05:52,120
Up!

124
00:05:54,160 --> 00:05:54,519
Slow down, slow down.

125
00:05:54,519 --> 00:05:55,279
Lao Lu!

126
00:06:05,720 --> 00:06:07,199
It really is because of that box!

127
00:06:10,879 --> 00:06:11,560
Fatty!

128
00:06:11,800 --> 00:06:13,079
Throw that box away!

129
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:15,439
They're going straight for that box!

130
00:06:15,439 --> 00:06:16,680
Throw that box away!

131
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:17,920
This, this, this...

132
00:06:19,480 --> 00:06:20,399
Throw it quickly!

133
00:06:36,680 --> 00:06:37,199
Fatty Bro, come back quickly!

134
00:06:37,199 --> 00:06:37,920
Hurry, hurry, hurry!

135
00:06:37,920 --> 00:06:38,560
Hurry, hurry, hurry!

136
00:06:39,199 --> 00:06:40,639
They really are going for that box!

137
00:06:40,639 --> 00:06:41,160
Hurry up!

138
00:06:41,360 --> 00:06:42,879
I said I shouldn't take that box!

139
00:06:42,879 --> 00:06:43,360
Hurry up!

140
00:06:43,360 --> 00:06:44,680
You insisted I take that box!

141
00:06:44,680 --> 00:06:45,160
Hurry up!

142
00:06:50,079 --> 00:06:51,079
Oh, my back!

143
00:06:51,720 --> 00:06:53,360
Tell me, these toads...

144
00:06:53,839 --> 00:06:56,040
Why are they so fixated on this box?

145
00:06:56,879 --> 00:06:57,560
Mr. Lu.

146
00:06:57,759 --> 00:06:59,680
I think those Red-backed Toads...

147
00:06:59,680 --> 00:07:00,839
...many generations ago...

148
00:07:00,839 --> 00:07:02,160
...were domesticated by humans.

149
00:07:02,160 --> 00:07:04,120
That's why their actions are purposeful.

150
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:07,240
They might be an endemic species here.

151
00:07:07,399 --> 00:07:10,079
Or maybe to adapt to the local environment.

152
00:07:10,079 --> 00:07:11,680
Like camels.

153
00:07:11,720 --> 00:07:12,720
Like reindeer.

154
00:07:12,920 --> 00:07:14,800
So these Red-backed Toads...

155
00:07:14,800 --> 00:07:17,279
...are very likely regional domesticated creatures.

156
00:07:17,279 --> 00:07:18,399
According to what you're saying...

157
00:07:18,560 --> 00:07:20,800
...they must have been domesticated since the Dian King era.

158
00:07:20,959 --> 00:07:21,839
It's possible.

159
00:07:21,839 --> 00:07:22,639
Fatty Bro.

160
00:07:22,720 --> 00:07:23,720
Are you tired?

161
00:07:24,079 --> 00:07:24,959
Let me carry your bag for a while.

162
00:07:24,959 --> 00:07:25,759
Sorry for the trouble.

163
00:07:25,959 --> 00:07:27,399
So many messy rocks.

164
00:07:27,439 --> 00:07:28,839
Which way do we go?

165
00:07:29,360 --> 00:07:30,759
Just keep going forward.

166
00:07:32,519 --> 00:07:34,560
I... I have low blood sugar.

167
00:07:35,160 --> 00:07:36,120
Low blood sugar?

168
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:38,639
According to the Mausoleum Chronicle...

169
00:07:39,160 --> 00:07:40,439
...once we exit this Gourd Cave...

170
00:07:40,639 --> 00:07:41,680
...it should be the Tomb Tower.

171
00:07:43,160 --> 00:07:44,199
You guys rest here for a bit.

172
00:07:44,199 --> 00:07:45,360
I'll go ahead and scout the way.

173
00:07:45,360 --> 00:07:46,000
Okay.

174
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:46,920
I'll go with you.

175
00:07:49,480 --> 00:07:50,240
Let me catch my breath.

176
00:07:52,720 --> 00:07:53,439
Lao Lu.

177
00:07:53,959 --> 00:07:55,079
Don't rest here.

178
00:07:55,279 --> 00:07:56,279
Let's hurry up and go.

179
00:07:56,279 --> 00:07:57,279
It's quite dangerous here.

180
00:07:57,279 --> 00:07:59,639
Why don't you have any sympathy?

181
00:08:00,519 --> 00:08:01,079
Just now inside...

182
00:08:01,079 --> 00:08:03,439
...that Giant Toad chased me like a dog.

183
00:08:03,439 --> 00:08:04,759
I even took a big fall.

184
00:08:04,759 --> 00:08:06,079
Now my back, my...

185
00:08:06,079 --> 00:08:07,680
It's still twisted.

186
00:08:07,959 --> 00:08:08,480
This...

187
00:08:08,720 --> 00:08:10,160
It almost killed me.

188
00:08:10,560 --> 00:08:11,480
Let's rest for a bit.

189
00:08:21,240 --> 00:08:22,279
You go check over there.

190
00:08:22,279 --> 00:08:23,000
I'll go this way.

191
00:08:23,519 --> 00:08:24,279
Okay, be careful.

192
00:08:42,039 --> 00:08:43,440
Help!

193
00:08:52,600 --> 00:08:53,159
Lao Lu!

194
00:08:53,159 --> 00:08:53,799
Mr. Lu!

195
00:09:01,639 --> 00:09:02,360
Watch out!

196
00:09:19,960 --> 00:09:20,519
Hurry up!

197
00:09:20,519 --> 00:09:20,960
Go!

198
00:09:20,960 --> 00:09:21,639
Dawei!

199
00:09:23,080 --> 00:09:23,840
I'm out of bullets!

200
00:09:23,840 --> 00:09:24,559
Catch!

201
00:09:27,840 --> 00:09:28,559
Run!

202
00:09:43,919 --> 00:09:44,559
Dawei!

203
00:09:44,919 --> 00:09:46,200
The blue toad is in the bag!

204
00:09:46,200 --> 00:09:47,159
Take it out!

205
00:09:55,320 --> 00:09:56,039
Give it to me!

206
00:10:19,759 --> 00:10:20,240
Are you crazy?

207
00:10:20,240 --> 00:10:21,159
Are you crazy?

208
00:10:21,159 --> 00:10:22,399
I told you to throw the box, did you?

209
00:10:22,639 --> 00:10:23,240
Did you throw it?

210
00:10:23,240 --> 00:10:24,279
Of course I threw it!

211
00:10:24,279 --> 00:10:25,200
I threw the box away!

212
00:10:25,200 --> 00:10:27,120
Are the things from the box still in the bag?

213
00:10:27,879 --> 00:10:29,039
Why does he have the bag?

214
00:10:29,039 --> 00:10:30,440
You put the stuff in the bag,

215
00:10:30,440 --> 00:10:31,440
and made him carry it!

216
00:10:31,440 --> 00:10:32,879
Are you playing with his life?

217
00:10:32,879 --> 00:10:33,840
Bro, bro!

218
00:10:34,440 --> 00:10:36,039
I volunteered to carry it for Fatty.

219
00:10:44,519 --> 00:10:45,519
Chen Youxi!

220
00:10:46,360 --> 00:10:47,799
We've known each other for thirty years!

221
00:10:49,240 --> 00:10:50,519
Is that what you think of me?

222
00:10:52,399 --> 00:10:53,159
Fine!

223
00:10:54,519 --> 00:10:55,440
I'm greedy for money.

224
00:10:56,200 --> 00:10:57,720
I put that thing in his bag on purpose,

225
00:10:57,720 --> 00:10:58,440
and made him carry it.

226
00:10:58,720 --> 00:11:00,720
I just wanted to see if the toad would chase him.

227
00:11:00,960 --> 00:11:02,159
If the toad catches him,

228
00:11:02,440 --> 00:11:03,720
and he dies here today,

229
00:11:03,720 --> 00:11:04,840
I'd be happy to see it!

230
00:11:05,039 --> 00:11:06,360
So he won't be an eyesore anymore!

231
00:11:06,759 --> 00:11:08,480
That's the kind of person I am, okay?

232
00:11:08,879 --> 00:11:09,639
Move aside!

233
00:11:11,840 --> 00:11:12,720
Fatty! Fatty!

234
00:11:12,720 --> 00:11:13,799
Don't stop me!

235
00:11:13,840 --> 00:11:15,919
From now on, you go your way,

236
00:11:15,960 --> 00:11:17,200
and I'll go mine.

237
00:11:17,240 --> 00:11:19,120
Whoever finds the Dian King's tomb first wins.

238
00:11:20,360 --> 00:11:20,960
Wait a minute.

239
00:11:21,440 --> 00:11:23,240
Staff Officer He, don't try to persuade me.

240
00:11:23,600 --> 00:11:24,399
We're done.

241
00:11:24,559 --> 00:11:25,679
I'm not trying to persuade you.

242
00:11:25,679 --> 00:11:26,759
I just want to tell you,

243
00:11:27,200 --> 00:11:28,440
we're already trapped here.

244
00:11:28,600 --> 00:11:29,519
There's nowhere to go.

245
00:11:40,399 --> 00:11:42,399
I saw a large stone door from a distance just now.

246
00:11:43,240 --> 00:11:44,159
Follow me.

247
00:12:12,039 --> 00:12:13,600
Three-Legged Toad.

248
00:12:14,720 --> 00:12:17,320
This groove is exactly the shape of the Three-Legged Toad.

249
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:19,080
I figured it out.

250
00:12:19,559 --> 00:12:20,440
Could it be...

251
00:12:20,600 --> 00:12:23,679
we need the Three-Legged Toad to open this door?

252
00:12:23,679 --> 00:12:24,600
Probably.

253
00:12:25,159 --> 00:12:27,440
We threw the... the toad away.

254
00:12:36,559 --> 00:12:37,399
Fatty.

255
00:13:25,159 --> 00:13:26,000
Think fast.

256
00:13:26,039 --> 00:13:27,440
How do we get it out?

257
00:13:54,159 --> 00:13:54,879
What now?

258
00:13:56,240 --> 00:13:57,039
Wanna race?

259
00:13:57,559 --> 00:13:58,399
Let's race!

260
00:13:59,440 --> 00:14:01,159
One, two...

261
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:11,679
Three!

262
00:14:13,279 --> 00:14:13,840
Run!

263
00:14:13,840 --> 00:14:14,679
Run!

264
00:14:23,840 --> 00:14:24,559
Old Chen!

265
00:14:24,759 --> 00:14:25,360
Catch!

266
00:14:26,600 --> 00:14:27,440
Shutong!

267
00:14:37,360 --> 00:14:38,919
The door is open, hurry!

268
00:14:44,399 --> 00:14:45,879
Bro! Fatty!

269
00:14:46,039 --> 00:14:46,840
Hurry up!

270
00:14:50,840 --> 00:14:52,120
Hurry, the door is closing!

271
00:14:53,200 --> 00:14:54,720
Bro! Chen Youxi!

272
00:14:55,080 --> 00:14:56,080
Old Chen, hurry!

273
00:14:56,279 --> 00:14:56,960
Bro!
